Revision history for RPi-Gyro-MPU6050

0.01 UNREL
    - Auto generated distribution with Dist::Mgr
    - Added the OO Perl interface; pure Perl, with the I2C transport
      provided by RPi::I2C
    - Added accel(), gyro(), temp(), tilt(), accel_range(), gyro_range(),
      calibrate_gyro(), gyro_offsets(), sleep(), wake(), reset(),
      register() and close()
    - Added hardware-free parameter validation and mocked register file
      logic test suites
    - Added examples/imu.pl and examples/tilt.pl
    - Added the TECHNICAL INFORMATION POD section with the MPU-6050
      register map, scaling tables, sample rate/filter, clocking and
      power details
    - Limited CI to Linux runners; RPi::I2C is a Linux-only XS dependency
    - Added RPi::Gyro::MPU6050::Deadband, a standalone hardware-free filter
      that reports only when a noisy reading has meaningfully changed
      (windowed smoothing + a +/- threshold with hysteresis), plus a
      deadband() convenience factory on the sensor object and t/15-deadband.t
    - Added examples/gyro_oled.pl (streams readings to an SSD1306 OLED) and
      examples/gyro_deadband_oled.pl (the same, but deadband-gated so the panel
      repaints only on real motion)
    - Documented sleep()/wake() in the SYNOPSIS (a "Powering down" block): sleep()
      drops the sensor to ~10uA keeping registers and calibration, wake() resumes
